		<principle>
	<title>Coulomb's Law</title>
	<statement>
		<p>The electric field created by a point charge <m>q_{\text{source}}</m> is given by <me>\vec{E}_{pc} = \frac{kq_{\text{source}}}{r^2}\hat{r}</me>  Here <m>k = 9 \cross 10^9 \frac{\text{Nm}^2}{\text{C}^2}}</m> is a constant and <m>\hat{r}</m> is a unit vector that points radially outward from the location of the point charge.</p>
	</statement>
</principle>


